<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Tutamun:
[I]Hi lar or anyone else from larian.

Do you have Poison and Diseas in your game?

If Yes:
How does Poison work?
It does its damage and then is gone, or does it keep damaging you until you find a cure poison potion or a Healer. There could be both sorts of poison in the world. Although I think that poisons that do their damage continuously should be very seldom. (Maybe only quest related.) I wouldn't like to carry antidotes around with me all the time. I think that it is enough if I have to carry Life- and Mana-Potions around with me. Antidotes normaly work for only one sort of poison and they don't hold very long (after a week they are useless). Maybe poison should be very slow, so that you have enough time to reach a healer. Some poisons may only make you weak and do not cause other damage. A poison could also loose its effect after a while if your body is strong enough.

Lots of different poison types to confuse the player.  ;)

You could put poison on your own weapons to make them more effective for a short while. This should only be possible on piercing weapons and not on blunt weapons.

A realy bad Monster that can only be defeated if you punch a poisoned Dagger in its tail.  ;) You would need a special poison that you only get if you complete a quest.

What about Diseas?
If you fight against Vampires/Werewolves you could be infected with lychantrope (hope this is correct) or become a vampire yourself. But this would limit your Char to only running around at night. Maybe he then could not complete the story anymore. Then there should be a way to get cured (eg. solve a hard quest).
If fighting against Undead or Rats you could also catch a diseas. If you run around in the rain for to long you could get a cold.

While you have a cold or a diseas some of your Char Stats could be lowered until you are cured. If the diseas is realy bad, you could very slowly loose life and mana points or get weaker and weaker...

The reaction of NPC's to you could be interesting too if they see that you have red spots all over your body  ;) "Don't come near me, I don't want to catch ..." Could be funny... Or they could throw stones at you, if you have the pest. *ouch*  >:)

If No:
Why not? Just curious.

Greetz from Tutamun, the Son of the Sun  ;)[/I][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
